Legacy Capital 


 















 














COMPANY PROFILE
Legacy Capital offers unparalleled investment banking services to private companies, specializing in mergers and acquisitions , private placements , business valuations and financial consulting . Our experienced team of professionals is dedicated to providing comprehensive representation and advisory services across a broad range of industries. We create solid relationships with our clients through personalized service and by delivering exceptional results. Legacy Capital was founded in 1994 and is based in New Orleans, Louisiana.
Legacy Capital is a registered member of FINRA (www.finra.org) , SIPC (www.sipc.org), and the Louisiana Office of Financial Institutions, Securities Division





Mergers & Acquisitions
Legacy assists companies in the sale of the majority or all of the equity or assets of a business. We strive to obtain the best possible terms for the selling shareholders by devising a selling process tailored to meet their specific goals and needs. We emphasize selecting the “right” buyer, who will consider the interests of management.




Private Placement
We assist private companies in raising equity from investors, private equity & venture capital firms. Entrepreneurs interested in raising private capital for start-up ventures or early stage companies can take advantage of exemptions from state and federal registration processes through a private placement offering.




Financial Consulting
Legacy provides valuation studies in connection with the contemplated sale of a company, a potential acquisition, a recapitalization or reorganization, or an evaluation of capital needs and sources. Legacy counsels corporate clients on developing and implementing short-term and long-term financing plans.







Legacy Capital Announces the Acquisition of Hunt telecommunications, LLC by Communications Sales & Leasing, Inc. 

 
New Orleans, LA – February 23, 2017 –Hunt Telecommunications, LLC (“Hunt”), a leading provider of data transport to K–12 schools and government agencies with a dense network of 140,000 fiber strand miles and 2,600 fiber route miles in Louisiana, has signed a definitive agreement to be acquired by Communications Sales & Leasing, Inc. (now renamed Uniti Group Inc.)  for initial consideration of $170 million in cash and equity plus additional contingent equity consideration upon the achievement of certain operational and financial milestones. 
 Legacy Capital served as Hunt’s exclusive financial advisor in connection with the transaction while Baldwin Haspel Burke and Mayer, LLC and Nowalsky & Gothard, APLLC acted as Hunt’s legal advisors. 
 The acquisition is expected to close during the third quarter of 2017 and is subject to customary closing conditions.
 http://investor.cslreit.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=253961&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=2248647
 










